<p>SILENT</p>
<p>silere is to be still as opposed to making noises.</p>
<p>tacere is to be silent as opposed to uttering words.</p>
<p>reticere refers to a person keeping something that might be said to himself.</p>
<p>obticere refers to keeping silent when asked to give an opinion, as opposed to answering.</p>
<p/>
<p>TACITURN</p>
<p>taciturnus refers to keeping silent as a habitual practice.</p>
<p>tacens refers to any oneone who does not currently speak.</p>
<p>tacitus refers to someone who keeps quite when he might expected to speak.</p>
